13/06/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister George Papandreou met on Thursday (12 June) with US State Department Special Co-ordinator for Cyprus Thomas Weston to discuss the next stages of the negotiation process and possible solutions to the longstanding dispute concerning the divided island.
Weston heads next to Ankara and Nicosia to exchange views.
In other news Thursday, Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis kicked off the ''24 EU Capital Tour'', aiming to co-ordinate preparations for next week's Thessaloniki summit.
His first stops were Belgium and Luxemburg;
on Friday he goes to Austria.
(ANA, MPA - 12/06/03)
